Front:
“How do I generate all unique permutations of an array with duplicates?”

Back:

Sort the array to group duplicates

Track used elements with a used[] array

Pick each unused element

Skip duplicates if the previous identical element wasn’t used

Recurse to build the next position

Undo choice (pop + mark unused)

Stop when all positions are filled → save

