This is Dijkstra but:

Minimize → becomes maximize

Addition → becomes multiplication

Use max-heap (or negative values)

Early stop when reaching end

Return 0 if unreachable

Time Complexity:

O(E log V)
🧠 One-Line Intuition

“Always move through the path with the highest success probability so far — the first time you reach the destination, that probability is the maximum possible.”


👉 Prim’s Algorithm – Minimum Cost to Connect Points (LeetCode 1584)

Efficiently calculate the minimum total cost to connect all points in 2D space using Manhattan distance.

Perfect when:

You have a set of points in 2D

Cost between points = |x1-x2| + |y1-y2|

You want to connect all points with minimum total cost

MST (Minimum Spanning Tree) concept applies

Classic Prim’s algorithm implementation.

✨ Flashcard

Front:
“How do I connect all points with minimum cost?”

Back:

Track visited points (MST nodes)

Keep minDist[i] → cheapest cost to connect point i to MST

Start from any point (here, point 0)

Pick closest unvisited point each step

Add cost and mark as visited

Update remaining points’ minDist with new distances

Repeat until all points are connected

⚡ Step-by-Step Combined Explanation
1️⃣ Initialization
n = len(points)
visited = set()
minDist = [inf]*n
minDist[0] = 0
totalCost = 0

Mental Map:

visited → points included in MST

minDist[i] → cheapest cost to connect point i

minDist[0] = 0 → starting point, cost 0

totalCost → accumulate MST total cost

2️⃣ Pick Closest Unvisited Point
curr = -1
currMin = inf
for i in range(n):
    if i not in visited and minDist[i] < currMin:
        currMin = minDist[i]
        curr = i

Mental Map:

Look at all unvisited points

Pick the one with smallest connection cost to MST

3️⃣ Add Point to MST
visited.add(curr)
totalCost += currMin

Mental Map:

Include this point in MST

Add its connection cost to totalCost

4️⃣ Update Distances of Remaining Points
for i in range(n):
    if i not in visited:
        x1, y1 = points[curr]
        x2, y2 = points[i]
        cost = abs(x1 - x2) + abs(y1 - y2)
        if cost < minDist[i]:
            minDist[i] = cost

Mental Map:

Check if connecting other unvisited points through this new point is cheaper

If yes → update minDist[i]

5️⃣ Repeat Until All Points Are Visited

Loop n times → each iteration adds one point to MST

After all points → totalCost is the answer

6️⃣ Return Result
return totalCost


🔑 Interview Tips

This is Prim’s algorithm for points

Use minDist array instead of heap for simplicity

Manhattan distance → |x1-x2| + |y1-y2|

Complexity: O(n^2)

Works well when n is moderate (~1000)

🧠 One-Line Intuition

“Always add the closest point to the MST so far — total cost grows minimally each step.”

