minDist = [0, inf, inf, inf]    # Start from point 0
totalCost = 0
Step 1: Pick node with smallest minDist

Look at minDist = [0, inf, inf, inf]

Smallest unvisited node = 0, cost = 0

Add to MST:

visited = {0}
totalCost = 0 + 0 = 0

Update distances:

Distance 0 → 1: |0-2| + |0-2| = 4 → minDist[1] = 4

Distance 0 → 2: |0-3| + |0-10| = 13 → minDist[2] = 13

Distance 0 → 3: |0-5| + |0-2| = 7 → minDist[3] = 7

Updated minDist: [0, 4, 13, 7]

Step 2: Pick next node with smallest minDist

