Block 5 — Characters Match
if str1[i-1] == str2[j-1]:

Example:

a == a

Then:

dp[i][j] = dp[i-1][j-1] + 1

Because LCS increases.

Block 6 — Characters Do Not Match
dp[i][j] = max(dp[i-1][j], dp[i][j-1])

Meaning:

Either ignore character from

str1
or
str2

Take the best.

Block 7 — Build the Supersequence
i, j = N, M
res = []

We start from bottom-right of the LCS table.

Block 8 — Traverse Backwards
while i > 0 and j > 0:
Case 1 — Characters Match
if str1[i-1] == str2[j-1]:

Add once:

res.append(str1[i-1])

Move diagonally:

i -= 1
j -= 1
Case 2 — Follow Larger LCS Direction
elif dp[i-1][j] > dp[i][j-1]:

Take from str1.

res.append(str1[i-1])
i -= 1

Else:

res.append(str2[j-1])
j -= 1
